  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\n\n2.13.0\n\n### What happened?\n\nI have read through all of the `npm` dependency issue fixes I can find here in the issues and elsewhere and I'm at a total loss. I have tried forcing fixes, I've tried installing individual versions of mocha. I can't run a single script in my program except to initialize a hardhat node. I just keep getting this error:\r\n\r\n### NPM ERR: ERESOLVE\r\n```\r\nnpm resolution error report\r\n\r\nWhile resolving: @nomicfoundation/hardhat-toolbox@1.0.2\r\nFound: @types/mocha@10.0.1\r\nnode_modules/@types/mocha\r\n  dev @types/mocha@\"^10.0.1\" from the root project\r\n\r\nCould not resolve dependency:\r\npeer @types/mocha@\"^9.1.0\" from @nomicfoundation/hardhat-toolbox@1.0.2\r\nnode_modules/@nomicfoundation/hardhat-toolbox\r\n  dev @nomicfoundation/hardhat-toolbox@\"^1.0.2\" from the root project\r\n\r\nConflicting peer dependency: @types/mocha@9.1.1\r\nnode_modules/@types/mocha\r\n  peer @types/mocha@\"^9.1.0\" from @nomicfoundation/hardhat-toolbox@1.0.2\r\n  node_modules/@nomicfoundation/hardhat-toolbox\r\n    dev @nomicfoundation/hardhat-toolbox@\"^1.0.2\" from the root project\r\n\r\nFix the upstream dependency conflict, or retry\r\nthis command with --force or --legacy-peer-deps\r\nto accept an incorrect (and potentially broken) dependency resolution.\r\n```\r\n\r\nAny idea for a fix would be greatly appreciated.\r\n\n\n### Minimal reproduction steps\n\nRunning any script except installing hardhat and running a hardhat node.\n\n### Search terms\n\nDependency, Mocha, Conflicting",
